  "task": "Implement Byzantine-resilient consensus with dynamic validator set management, adaptive fault tolerance, and provably immutable finality. Extend v14 by requiring: (1) Dynamic Validator Set with Atomic Safety—add and remove validators during live consensus while provably maintaining Byzantine safety (f < n/3 always holds); prove that all active validators have causally-consistent view of membership changes; (2) Adaptive Byzantine Threshold Recalculation—automatically recalculate max faults f_new = floor((n_new - 1) / 3) during set changes; ensure no liveness gap where threshold is undefined; prevent validator removal that would violate f < n/3 invariant; (3) Leader Equivocation Under Byzantine Leadership—detect if leader itself is Byzantine by identifying conflicting blocks, votes, or proposals it sent; prove equivocation using cryptographic signature analysis; trigger deterministic replacement without consensus halt; (4) Immutable Finality Anchors—mark blocks as finalized only after f+1 validators sign; prove that finalized blocks cannot be rolled back even if f validators later become Byzantine; include cryptographic proof of finality irreversibility; (5) Cascading Failure Resilience—correctly handle validators failing and recovering in rapid sequence (e.g., 3+ faults within 2 rounds); prove liveness is not lost; prove safety is not violated; characterize timing constraints that prevent cascade-induced splits.",
